commit.message:
ghostscript-9.50 updates

Since version 9.50 GS defaults to -dSAFER and produces a warning
messages if -dWRITESYSTEMDICT is used, which ends up in the output
file after the psfrem stage, messing it up.

The proper way to get WRITESYSTEMDICT now is to specify -dNOSAFER
explicitly and do .setsafer once we're done with the systemdict.

The patch also fixes a minor issue with psfrem not truncating its
output.

rename runopts.stdout

`stdout` may be a macro.
fix mkstemps proto warning on MacOS
allow setting paper size via environment variable
explicit mode bits for installed files

restore --header/--footer options

Also fix filename/pageno handling in headers and footers.

The original quick and dirty code had filename and pageno as special
case for headers and footers, and it was not configurable.

minor wextra and valgrind fixes

Also fix segfault w/ unknow longopts.
fix return-NULL in a void func
remove explicit argument indexing from printf
no need to run resources, gs has -I../res for that
